@NODE "intro" "Introduction"
@NEXT "required"
@PREV "MAIN"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{B}Introduction@{UB}

I was tired at having to mess around with arexx scripts and having to click on loads of icons to
load in Miami/IBrowse/YAM/Go Online/ etc . . . So I wrote NetLink.

I have tried to make a program which will load/online/offline Miami and give you information
about the call in one interface.

NetLink allows the user to choose a certain ISP for a given time period, to avoid the slower ISPs.
NetLink will calculate the cost of the call and create a log file too.
NetLink will automatically re-connect to your choosen ISP when required.
I think it is quite nice.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "required" "Requirements"
@PREV "MAIN"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{B}Requirements@{UB}

NetLink is a MUI program.
You will need MUI 3.7.

You will also need Miami.
You will also need TimeText.mcc  (included)
You will also need Lamp.mcc      (included)

I am not sure if I should include the *.mcc's but they are availiable on Aminet.

Please remove all traces of NetLink if you have used this before, as the prefs are NOT compatible.
The prefs files is ENV:NetLink.prefs.

I think that is about it.  Oh an Amiga.

@ENDNODE

